---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { url } from '../lib/url';
---
<Base title="About" description="What REALMS is, who built it, and how to cite it.">
  <article class="article">
    <div class="prose">
      <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'About' }]} />
      <h1>About REALMS</h1>

      <p>
        <strong>REALMS</strong> — Research Entity Archive for Light & Metaphysical
        Spirit Hierarchies — is a provenance-tracked knowledge base of spiritual
        entities documented across global indigenous and traditional religious
        traditions. Every entry records <em>what</em> was said, <em>where</em> it
        was said, and <em>who</em> said it.
      </p>

      <h2>What this is not</h2>
      <p>
        This is not a generative text site. No entity page is the product of an
        unconstrained language model. Every claim on an entity page traces to
        at least one recorded source, and the exact model, temperature, and
        prompt version used for extraction are stored alongside the result.
        Where we merge multiple extractions into a single description we say so.
      </p>

      <h2>Where the text comes from</h2>
      <p>
        The ingestion pipeline fetches open source-text layers (Wikipedia, the
        Internet Archive's public-domain scans, PubMed abstracts), breaks them
        into chunks, and asks an LLM to produce structured entity records from
        each chunk. Records are then normalized, fuzzy-matched against existing
        entities, and merged. Typed relationships come from explicit role fields
        in the extraction prompt. Unclear cases are flagged for human review.
      </p>

      <h2>How to read an entity page</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Confidence ribbon</strong> — a tier (triangulated / corroborated / single tradition / stub) reflecting how many independent source-types agree.</li>
        <li><strong>Sidenotes</strong> — alternate names, region, tradition, external identifiers.</li>
        <li><strong>Relationships</strong> — typed edges only (parent_of, consort_of, etc). Weak co-occurrence edges live in the graph view.</li>
        <li><strong>Sources</strong> — citations and verbatim passages extracted from source texts.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Links</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href={url('/about/methodology/')}>Methodology in detail</a></li>
        <li><a href={url('/about/ethics/')}>Ethics — indigenous knowledge, living traditions</a></li>
        <li><a href={url('/about/cite/')}>How to cite REALMS</a></li>
        <li><a href={url('/sources/')}>Source catalogue</a></li>
        <li><a href={url('/collections/')}>Collections — thematic groupings</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/apeters247/realms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Source code (GitHub)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">License: CC-BY-4.0</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
